<div class="recipe">
<p>What's better than homemade pizza? Seriously, we can't think of anything. With this recipe, you can have fresh, homemade pizza in a weekday-friendly manner.</p>
<p>What is a fermented dough? Simply, it is a dough that you leave to rest in the fridge for a few days, and up to a week. The flavours that develop overtime from this process creates something you've never experienced before from a more traditional dough. As the yeast consumes the sugar, it starts to take on an almost alcoholic scent. While the dough won't get tipsy, it takes on a ton of new flavour that these simple ingredients won't get you on their own.</p>
<p>Apart from the better flavour, the fermentation process takes days to take effect. So, we recommend making this dough on the weekend, then using it during the week. With the dough taken care of, assembling and cooking your pizzas will take less than 30 minutes - that's right, you can have homemade pizzas on a weeknight, in less than 30 minutes. What's not to love?</p>
<p>Don't be daunted by the thought of making great pizza dough at home. Really, it's quite simple. In terms of special equipment, we recommend grabbing yourself an instant read thermometer. While not essential, it'll prevent you from accenditally killing the yeast with the hot water. We also recommend using a stand mixer with a dough hook attachment to make the kneading process easier. However, that can be all done by hand.</p>
<p>This recipe just covers the pizza dough, if you want to see how we recommend cooking your new favourite pizza recipe, check out our cast-iron sausage pizza recipe here.</p>
<p>This recipe will make 6 9-inch pizzas.</p>
