<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>2 1/4 cups warm water (at 105F-115F)</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon sugar</li>
        <li>1 packet (or a tablespoon) of active dry yeast</li>
        <li>2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon salt</li>
        <li>5 cups bread flour (or all purpose - bread flour makes for a chewier crust)</li>
        <li>herbs and spices, optional (no more than a teaspoon or two)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Warm your water to 105F-115F and lightly mix with the sugar and yeast in a large bowl. Allow the yeast to bloom (froth up) for about 5 minutes. If it doesn't get frothy, your yeast is likely dead and you will need to start fresh with some new yeast.</li>
        <li>Add the rest of the dough ingredients and mix until a shaggy dough forms. You may need to add more flour if it is too sticky, but try to add as little as possible. Letting the dough rest for a bit will cause the flour to hydrate and will make it easier to work.</li>
        <li>Knead the dough until you can see light through it when stretched thin. This should be about 10 minutes of kneading</li>
        <li>Split the dough into 6 lightly oiled containers and store in the fridge for up to one week.</li>
    </ol>
</div>
